d Persia</span></div><div class="style24"><span id="tekst69">     <span id="tekst70"><span id="tekst71">     <span id="tekst72">    <span id="tekst73">     <a href="http://www.litant.eu/En/artykuly/nr8/Proc.pdf">( plik pdf )</a></span></span></span></span></span></div><div class="style24"><br /></div><span id="tekst30">     <div class="MsoNormal"><b>    <span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;; line-height: 115%;">    Piotr Stepien</span></b></div><div class="MsoNormal">    <span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;; line-height: 115%;">    (Adam Mickiewicz University, Poznan)</span></div><div class="MsoNormal">    <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;; line-height: 115%;">    The metric-rhythmical structure of Pindar’s O. 2 and its echoes      in Aeschylus’ and Euripides’     <i>Supplices</i></span></div><div class="style7">    <a href="http://www.litant.eu/En/artykuly/nr8/Stepien.pdf">( plik pdf )</a></div><div class="style7">    &nbsp;</div><div class="MsoNormal"><b>    <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;; line-height: 115%;">    Marcin Wasilewski</span></b></div><div class="MsoNormal">    <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;; line-height: 115%;">    (University of Lodz)</span></div><div class="MsoNormal">    <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;; line-height: 115%;">    Currents of Greek Pedagogy. The Outline of methodological and      bibliographical issues</span></div></span>    <div class="MsoNormal">    <span id="tekst37">     <a href="http://www.litant.eu/En/artykuly/nr8/Wasilewski.pdf">( plik pdf )</a></span></div></span><span style="font-size: x-small;">    </span><div class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><br /></span></div><span style="font-size: x-small;">&nbsp;</span><span id="tekst2"><span 